page.title: 16Whiteparish common-continued
page.content: In Whiteparish common the bird that is most famous is the Nightingale.The Nightingale sings as much in the day as night.The Nightingale is a woodland bird,the cock birds arrive from Africa in mid April and they are the singers, the Female birds arrive ten days later.The nightingale's song is easily recognised in the woods.One of the Nightingale's notes is deep and another is a drawn out note.The Nightingale is not an easy bird to see. It conceals itself in the undergrowth and builds it's nest in the leaves and grasses on the ground. The mothers can be aggressive in defence of it's young. Other birds that we have seen in our area are the Lapwing,the Heron and the Kingfisher.
